Pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling, add @salt{0.25%tsp}, stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, trim the @Courgette{1}(trimmed) then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces. Halve the @Red Chilli{½}(halved and deseeded) lengthways, deseed then finely chop. Zest and halve the @Lime{½}(zest and juice reserved). Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the @British Beef Mince{240%g} into a #bowl{} with the @Plain Flour{8%g}, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and mix together. Shape into 4 balls per person. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium high heat and once hot, add the meatballs and cook until golden brown all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{} and set aside.

Return the frying pan to medium high heat and add a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} if the pan is dry. Once hot, add the courgette and stir fry until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the garlic, @Red Thai Style Paste{50%g} and half the chilli. Cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}. Add the @Coconut Milk{200%ml} and @Water for the Curry{500%ml} then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Return the meatballs to the pan, cover with a lid (or some foil), bring to a simmer, reduce the heat to medium and cook until the meatballs are cooked and the sauce has reduced slightly, ~{6-8%minutes}, stirring occasionally. IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the rice is cooked, fluff it up with a #fork{} and carefully stir the lime zest through it. When the curry is ready, squeeze in some lime juice and stir through the @Soy Sauce{12.5%ml}. Cut any remaining lime into wedges.

Divide the rice between #bowls{} and serve the curry on top. Top with any remaining chilli and serve with any lime wedges alongside for squeezing over. Enjoy!